President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden visited the Louisville Recreation & Senior Center in Louisville, Colorado, to survey the damage caused by the Marshall Fire. The President expressed his sympathy for the devastation caused by the fire and praised the courage and resolve of the community. He emphasized the need for support and assistance in rebuilding the affected areas. The President also acknowledged the role of firefighters and first responders in fighting the fire and thanked them for their efforts. He highlighted the importance of taking action to address climate change and promote renewable energy as part of the recovery and rebuilding process. The First Lady also expressed her condolences for the loss of pets and praised the strength of the community. The President promised to provide federal assistance and support for the recovery efforts.